  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Gravitational lock between two modulation sources. LFO1 at 2.0 Hz (maximum) creates rapid filter movement. LFO2 at exactly 1.0 Hz creates a pressure modulation at half the filter rate. The 2:1 frequency ratio creates a tidally locked system — the filter breathes twice for every pressure cycle, producing a complex but repeating polyrhythmic texture. Aftertouch increases pressure compression, breaking the tidal lock into chaos.",
  "tags": [
    "bass",
    "rhythmic",
    "polyrhythm",
    "modulation",
    "tidal",
    "guru-bin",
    "transcendental"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OCEANDEEP — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": ["Sutra 4: Integer LFO Ratios Create Stable Polyrhythms", "D006: Expression Input Is Not Optional"],
    "revelation": "Tempora spoke: LFO1 at 2.0 Hz and LFO2 at 1.0 Hz form a 2:1 ratio — the same relationship as Earth-Moon tidal locking. The filter oscillates at double the compression rate, creating a breathing pattern where every other filter sweep coincides with a pressure peak. The result is a polyrhythmic texture that never drifts because the ratio is exact. But aftertouch breaks the lock by adding non-periodic pressure — chaos from expression.",
    "god": "Tempora",
    "flock_note": "The Breath mapped the polyrhythm: beat 1 — filter up + pressure up. Beat 2 — filter up + pressure down. Beat 3 — filter up + pressure up. The pattern creates a compound rhythm from two simple sinusoidal LFOs. The Tongue confirmed: aftertouch disrupts the clean ratio by adding DC offset to the pressure, making the compression respond to touch rather than cycle.",
    "diagnosis": "This sound was a modulated bass. It is now a tidal system — two gravitationally locked oscillations producing compound rhythm from simple ratios, with the performer's touch as the gravitational perturbation."
  },
